==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|pelote||small ball|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|VL.|en}} *{{term|pilotta|lang=la}}, diminutive of {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|pila||ball|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
*: {{rhymes|ɛlɪt|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A small, compressed, hard chunk of matter.
#: ''a '''pellet''' of wood, paper, or ore''
# A lead [[projectile]] used as ammunition in rifled air guns.
# Compressed byproduct of digestion regurgitated by owls.  Serves as a waste disposal mechanism for indigestible parts of food, such as fur and bones.
# {{context|heraldiccharge|lang=en}} A [[roundel]] [[sable]] (black circular spot; also called [[ogress]]).

